<http://data.europa.eu/s1n> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/license> <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2026-05-14" .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/Dataflow> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://data.europa.eu/s1n> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/Dataflow> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/Dataflow> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Dataflow"@en .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/Dataflow> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An abstract concept of the Data Sets, i.e. a structure without any data."@en .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/Dataflow> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Catalog> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/statUnitMeasure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://data.europa.eu/s1n> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/statUnitMeasure> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/statUnitMeasure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "unit of measurement"@en .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/statUnitMeasure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "a unit of measurement of the observations in the dataset, for example Euro, square kilometre,\r\npurchasing power standard (PPS), full-time equivalent, percentage. \r\nUnit of measurement is a \"conceptual\" entity that applies to all distribution formats,\r\ne.g. in the case when a dataset is provided both in SDMX and in Data Cube."@en .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/statUnitMeasure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/statUnitMeasure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/numSeries> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://data.europa.eu/s1n> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/numSeries> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/numSeries> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "number of data series"@en .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/numSeries> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "represents the number of distinct time series available in the dataset that contain data.\r\nA distinct time series is defined as a unique combination of dimension values (such as country, sex, age, unit of measure, etc.) that has at least one observation value or attribute associated with it - where an attribute may include a flag even in the absence of an actual data value. Time (e.g., year) is treated as one dimension among others, not as a unit of aggregation."@en .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/numSeries> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/numSeries> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/measure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://data.europa.eu/s1n> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/measure> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/measure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "measure"@en .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/measure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "a component that represents the phenomenon being observed.\r\n\r\nMeasure is a \"conceptual\" entity that applies to all distribution formats, e.g. in case a dataset is provided both in SDMX and in DataCube."@en .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/measure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/measure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://purl.org/linked-data/cube#MeasureProperty> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/dimension> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://data.europa.eu/s1n> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/dimension> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/dimension> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "dimension"@en .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/dimension> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "a component that identifies observations, e.g. the time to which the observation applies , or a geographic region which the observation covers.\r\n\r\nDimension is a \"conceptual\" entity that applies to all distribution formats, e.g. in case a dataset is provided both in SDMX and in DataCube. "@en .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/dimension> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/dimension> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://purl.org/linked-data/cube#DimensionProperty> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/dataStructureDefinition> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://data.europa.eu/s1n> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/dataStructureDefinition> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/dataStructureDefinition> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "data structure definition"@en .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/dataStructureDefinition> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a statistical dataset to the Data Structure Definition (DSD) that defines its dimensions, attributes, measures, and overall observation structure."@en .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/dataStructureDefinition> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/dataStructureDefinition> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://purl.org/linked-data/cube#DataStructureDefinition> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/attribute> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://data.europa.eu/s1n> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/attribute> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/attribute> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "attribute"@en .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/attribute> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "a component used to qualify and interpret observed values, e.g. units of measure, any scaling factors and metadata such as the status of the observation (e.g. estimated, provisional).\r\nAttribute is a \"conceptual\" entity that applies to all distribution formats, e.g. in case a dataset is provided both in SDMX and in DataCube."@en .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/attribute> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset> .
<http://data.europa.eu/s1n/attribute> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://purl.org/linked-data/cube#AttributeProperty> .
